<section id=3D"2.-Independencies-in-Bayesian-Networks">
<h3>2. Independencies in Bayesian Networks<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"h=
ttps://pgmpy.org/detailed_notebooks/2.%20Bayesian%20Networks.html#2.-Indepe=
ndencies-in-Bayesian-Networks" title=3D"Link to this heading">=C2=B6</a></h=
3>
<p>Independencies implied by the network structure of a Bayesian Network ca=
n be categorized in 2 types:</p>
<ol class=3D"arabic">
<li><p><strong>Local Independencies:</strong> Any variable in the network i=
s independent of its non-descendents given its parents. Mathematically it c=
an be written as:</p>
<div class=3D"math">
<p><img src=3D"https://pgmpy.org/_images/math/7b9b4eb30d1772f16fb63ce773c63=
a1e3261150f.png" alt=3D"(X \perp NonDesc(X) | Pa(X)"></p>
</div><p>where <img class=3D"math" src=3D"https://pgmpy.org/_images/math/96=
f5ddb3f60f1a021cbd6915b2c9aea56329175c.png" alt=3D"NonDesc(X)"> is the set =
of variables which are not descendents of <img class=3D"math" src=3D"https:=
//pgmpy.org/_images/math/ed38fa24f1c94891bd312012aab3f6673be3eb83.png" alt=
=3D"X"> and <img class=3D"math" src=3D"https://pgmpy.org/_images/math/b1bd8=
f322335a0176c22f3593ac312d261b0df3d.png" alt=3D"Pa(X)"> is the set of varia=
bles which are parents of <img class=3D"math" src=3D"https://pgmpy.org/_ima=
ges/math/ed38fa24f1c94891bd312012aab3f6673be3eb83.png" alt=3D"X">.</p>
</li>
<li><p><strong>Global Independencies:</strong> For discussing global indepe=
ndencies in Bayesian Networks we need to look at the various network struct=
ures possible. Starting with the case of 2 nodes, there are only 2 possible=
 ways for it to be connected:</p></li>
</ol>
<div class=3D"nbinput docutils container">
<div class=3D"prompt highlight-none notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><=
pre id=3D"codecell28"><span></span>[42]:
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
