<p>In the above two cases it is fairly obvious that change in any of the no=
de will affect the other. For the first case we can take the example of <im=
g class=3D"math" src=3D"https://pgmpy.org/_images/math/d959b626eed2cbc2c5d4=
76387fdc50021272ecc1.png" alt=3D"difficulty \rightarrow grade">. If we incr=
ease the difficulty of the course the probability of getting a higher grade=
 decreases. For the second case we can take the example of <img class=3D"ma=
th" src=3D"https://pgmpy.org/_images/math/9fd7ef74a7f8ae3cbbfa4ac4e07ad5bba=
1bf159c.png" alt=3D"SAT \leftarrow Intel">. Now if we increase the probabil=
ity of getting a good score in SAT that would imply that the student is int=
elligent, hence increasing the
probability of <img class=3D"math" src=3D"https://pgmpy.org/_images/math/15=
68503af3041c6eac4e2a670d46e25d9b8f3b73.png" alt=3D"i_1">. Therefore in both=
 the cases shown above any change in the variables leads to change in the o=
ther variable.</p>
<p>Now, there are four possible ways of connection between 3 nodes:</p>
